## ATypedArrayTuple.some() method

Determines whether the specified callback function returns true for any element of an array.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
abstract some(callbackfn: (value: number, index: number, array: T) => boolean, thisArg?: unknown): boolean;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  callbackfn | (value: number, index: number, array: T) =&gt; boolean | A function that accepts up to three arguments. The some method calls the callbackfn function for each element in array1 until the callbackfn returns true, or until the end of the array. |
|  thisArg | unknown | An object to which the this keyword can refer in the callbackfn function. If thisArg is omitted, undefined is used as the this value. |

<b>Returns:</b>

boolean
